This is pretty minor, but would be nice nonetheless.  When renaming pages in Confluence, it offers you the option of renaming the links.  When it does that, it would be nice it would check to see if the result contains any redundant visible links.

By way of example, we had some pages in Confluence that we couldn't update or rename without rebooting the server (which has hopefully gone away since the upgrade).  So we had a document that was once XML and couldn't be altered.  As a workaround, we created a few pages like XML V2. In some cases, we went back to links in other pages and adjusted them so that instead of being a link like [XML] (to the broken page) they were [XML|XML V2].  After a reboot, we were able to remove the original page and rename the new page back XML V2 -> XML.  When doing that, Confluence renamed the links, resulting in [XML|XML].  This is technically correct, but not ideal.  [XML] would have been a better result.

So ... very minor, but would be nice if it could do this.

